  "subjects_top_term": "Insanity defense", 
  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1983-02-08", 
    "text": "Amends the Federal criminal code to make it a defense to a Federal prosecution that the defendant, as a result of mental disease or defect, lacked substantial capacity to appreciate the criminality of his conduct. Places the burden of providing insanity on the defendant. Authorizes a special verdict of \"not guilty by reason of insanity.\" Prohibits witnesses from offering opinions on whether the defendant lacked substantial capacity to appreciate the criminality of his conduct."
  }, 
